	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, first of, that test should be number 10 (counting from 1), be sure to be using Nestress lastest version (you can get it from the main page).
<br />
<br />About that test, I'm not sure at all, but I guess it resets VRAM address by reading register 0x2002, and then sets the new address by writing twice to register 0x2005. Check Loopy's Scrolling texts for more info on how PPU I/O registers work.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
